            h1 Adding Placeholders
            h5 Adding Placeholders allows you to add new Placeholders to the database when Placeholders you need are not already available to users. Placeholders are automatically added when DARS reports are parsed when using the Add Student feature. If you add the same Placeholder with the same Placeholder code and catalog year it will update the other values in the database. This will allow you to change any values which are wrong or need changing. You can of Placeholder add a new Placeholder that isn't in the database already. Available Placeholders can also be seen when in the Program Of study you double click on a blank input box for the Placeholder code.
        .row
          .col-md-6(style='padding-top: 2%;')
            img(src='/assets/courseedit/placeholders/add_top3.png', alt='Picture Not Found', width='60%', height='100%')
          .col-md-6(style='padding-top: 10%;')
            h1 Adding A Placeholder I
            h5 Here we have the first three fields when adding or updating a Placeholder. Placeholder Codes must contain no spaces and the program should enforce this by not allowing you to enter any spaces. This is due to the fact that the DARS reports use no spaces in their Placeholder codes so we must follow suit to keep the databse in check. The Placeholder Name can be anything but cannot conain '/'. The Placeholder Hours must be a number or decimal number. Again these ruels are enforced but are stated here for your convenience.
        .row
          .col-md-6(style='padding-top: 5%;')
            img(src='/assets/courseedit/placeholders/add_bottom4.png', alt='Picture Not Found', width='60%', height='100%')
          .col-md-6(style='padding-top: 15%;')
            h1 Adding A Placeholder II
            h5 Here we have the last four fields when adding or updating a Placeholder. Tier can contain anything except '/'s and spaces. Placeholder Prereq's are the Placeholders Pre-requisites and must contain no '/'s. Catalog Year must follow the format of '2015-16' this is also due to how the DARS reports contain the catalog years and the database must stay consistent across the program. This format is enforced and even palces the '-' in for you. All you need to do it type all six numbers. The last option is the heading option. This will show ALL available headings in the database. Placeholders are matched to headings so you must choose an availabe heading so that your Placeholder will show up in the right table inside the Program Of Study.

